-- Russia May Boost Spending on Weapons to $656 Billion Over Decade, RIA Says
-- Lyubov Pronina
-- 2010-07-19T14:02:51Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-19/russia-may-boost-spending-on-weapons-to-656-billion-over-decade-ria-says.html

          
          
             Russiaâ€™s government may increase the
Defense Ministry budget for arms purchases this decade by about
half to 20 trillion rubles ($656 billion), RIA Novosti reported,
citing Deputy Defense Minister Vladimir Popovkin.  
 That figure, for the period 2011-2020, includes about 70
fifth-generation fighter jets, 20 Ruslan heavy-lift cargo
aircraft and 1,000 helicopters, Popovkin said at the Farnborough
Air Show in the U.K. today, according to the state-run Russian
news wire.  
